{"id": "lpl1665702560927", "title": "commit", "breadcrumbs": ["Uniface Reference", "ProcScript Reference", "ProcScript: Statements", "commit"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpl1665702560927.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">commit</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous: colorbox \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous: colorbox \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zfr1695290811319.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next: compare \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next: compare \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bjk1719388692175.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpl1665702560927.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpl1665702560927.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpl1665702560927.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3614401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lpl1665702560927.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lpl1665702560927.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lpl1665702560927.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lpl1665702560927\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__commit_212216\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Commit a transaction to a DBMS or path.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__topic_d70256e1_d70257e1_d70258e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__codeblock_qk5_bxz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">commit  {\"PathString\"}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__p_d70262e1_d70263e1_d70264e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">commit \"DEF\"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__topic_d46087e1_d46088e1_d46089e1_d46090e1_d46091e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e72\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6212e1_d6213e1_d6214e1__entry__3\">\n Required path name:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__li_d31817e1_d31818e1_d31819e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var> starts with a dollar sign (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code>), the argument is assumed to be a path name. Modifications to all entities accessed through that path are committed. In this case, assignments determine which entities are committed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__li_d31820e1_d31821e1_d31822e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var> does not start with a dollar sign, the argument is assumed to be a DBMS defined in the modeled entities. Modifications to all entities assigned to that DBMS are committed. In this case, the modeled entity definition determines which entities are committed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__li_d31823e1_d31824e1_d31825e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">PathString</var> is omitted, all pending updates for all databases used in the transaction are written (committed) and all locked occurrences are unlocked.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__topic_d46092e1_d46093e1_d46094e1_d46095e1_d46096e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e150\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__2\">\n The data was successfully committed.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-3</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__2\">\n Exceptional I/O error (hardware or software).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-9</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__2\">\n An attempt to open a DBMS failed because the maximum number of DBMS logons has already been reached.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6215e1_d6216e1_d6217e1__entry__2\">\n Network error: unknown.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Values commonly returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> following\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__2\">\n Error constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__3\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-2</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">-12</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UIOSERR_*&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__3\">\n Errors during database I/O.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code> through  <code class=\"ph codeph\">-30</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UNETERR_*&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__3\">\n Errors during network I/O.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-1107</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_PATH&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lpl1665702560927__table_d6218e1_d6219e1_d6220e1__entry__3\">\n The path name is not correct or the path does not exist, for example, no assignment is found for the path.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__topic_d46097e1_d46098e1_d46099e1_d46100e1_d46101e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e360\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__topic_d46102e1_d46103e1_d46104e1_d46105e1_d46106e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e370\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__p_d70280e1_d70281e1_d70282e1\">If a target DBMS does not support database locking, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> statement is ignored. For information about your DBMS, see the appropriate DBMS Driver Guide.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__p_d70283e1_d70284e1_d70285e1\">To avoid currency problems, add a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> (or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> statement) at the highest component level for the current transaction. For example, if Component B is activated by Component A, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> statement should be in Component A rather than Component B.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__p_d70286e1_d70287e1_d70288e1\">However, if the component's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component Behavior</span> property is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Keep component definition and data in memory</code>, you should use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> at that component's level.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__section_i1q_w2b_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e406\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span>\n</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows the use of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span>\n            statement:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__pre_wk2_x2b_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger store\n call CENSTORE\n return ($status)\nend; store\n\nfunction CENSTORE\nstore\nif ($status &lt; 0)\n message \"Store error!\"\n rollback\nelse\n message \"Store complete.\"\n commit\n if ($status &lt; 0)\n message \"Commit error, rollback performed.\"\n rollback\n endif\nendif\nend; CENSTORE\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__section_fqt_xdb_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d448434e424\">Example: Committing DEF versus $DEF</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Consider the modeled entities with the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Model Name</span>\n            property set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">MYMODEL</code>. These entities are assigned to the default\n            DBMS. At runtime, assignments are used to redirect the entity FRODO to another DBMS:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__pre_zt1_ydb_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$DEF = $ORA\nFRODO.MYMODEL = $SYB</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">If the following <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> statement is used, all\n            entities in MYMODEL (which are assigned to the default DBMS) are committed:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__pre_a51_ydb_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">commit \"DEF\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">If the following <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> statement is used, all\n            entities except FRODO are committed:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lpl1665702560927__pre_b51_ydb_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; commit all entities of MYMODEL except FRODO\ncommit \"$DEF\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/csi1665702634389.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>rollback</a><p>Undo the transaction (if supported by DBMS).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Control</a><p>A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614401\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "commit Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Commit a transaction to a DBMS or path. commit {\"PathString\"} Copy Example: commit \"DEF\" Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description PathString String Required path name: If PathString starts with a dollar sign ( $ ), the argument is assumed to be a path name. Modifications to all entities accessed through that path are committed. In this case, assignments determine which entities are committed. If PathString does not start with a dollar sign, the argument is assumed to be a DBMS defined in the modeled entities. Modifications to all entities assigned to that DBMS are committed. In this case, the modeled entity definition determines which entities are committed. If PathString is omitted, all pending updates for all databases used in the transaction are written (committed) and all locked occurrences are unlocked. Return Values Table 2. Values returned in $status Value Meaning 0 The data was successfully committed. -3 Exceptional I/O error (hardware or software). -9 An attempt to open a DBMS failed because the maximum number of DBMS logons has already been reached. -16 Network error: unknown. Table 3. Values commonly returned by $procerror following commit Value Error constant Meaning -2 through -12 <UIOSERR_*> Errors during database I/O. -16 through -30 <UNETERR_*> Errors during network I/O. -1107 <UPROCERR_PATH> The path name is not correct or the path does not exist, for example, no assignment is found for the path. Use Allowed in all component types. Description If a target DBMS does not support database locking, the commit statement is ignored. For information about your DBMS, see the appropriate DBMS Driver Guide. To avoid currency problems, add a commit (or rollback statement) at the highest component level for the current transaction. For example, if Component B is activated by Component A, the commit statement should be in Component A rather than Component B. However, if the component's Component Behavior property is set to Keep component definition and data in memory , you should use commit at that component's level. Example: Using commit The following example shows the use of the commit statement: trigger store call CENSTORE return ($status) end; store function CENSTORE store if ($status < 0) message \"Store error!\" rollback else message \"Store complete.\" commit if ($status < 0) message \"Commit error, rollback performed.\" rollback endif endif end; CENSTORE Copy Example: Committing DEF versus $DEF Consider the modeled entities with the Model Name property set to MYMODEL . These entities are assigned to the default DBMS. At runtime, assignments are used to redirect the entity FRODO to another DBMS: $DEF = $ORA FRODO.MYMODEL = $SYB Copy If the following commit statement is used, all entities in MYMODEL (which are assigned to the default DBMS) are committed: commit \"DEF\" Copy If the following commit statement is used, all entities except FRODO are committed: ; commit all entities of MYMODEL except FRODO commit \"$DEF\" Copy Related Links rollback Undo the transaction (if supported by DBMS). Transaction Control A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}